annotationA: GH06691p; Guanylate kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: purine nucleotide metabolic process
annotationB: cGMP-specific 3',5'-cyclic phosphodiesterase; Hydrolyzes the second messager cGMP, which is a key regulator of many important physiological processes. Has cAMP phosphodiesterase activity in vitro but not in vivo. Has a role regulating cGMP transport in Malpighian tubule principal cells
